; Minimal spawnable for the dual-instance node-replication harness (increment 3).
;
; Deliberately a BARE Node3D, not the real scenes/Player.tscn. The harness proves
; that MultiplayerSpawner replicates a server-spawned node's *existence* (and its
; peer-id name — the identity contract in NetworkManager.SpawnPlayer) to a real
; connected client. The spawner does NOT replicate transform/state — that rides
; the game's own RPC tick loop, which increment 2 (NetStateSyncTest) already
; proves. So instancing the heavyweight Player.tscn (FBX + AnimationTree) here
; would only add unrelated headless surface for no extra coverage. The root must
; be a Node3D because NetworkManager.SpawnPlayer sets Position on it.

[node name="HarnessPlayer" type="Node3D"]
